<br>
 Behind her stood her son, much older then last seen. Skylar had grown to the age of three as he cling onto his mother's legs, watching the group with those same green orbs. Silent they both stayed, both mother and son observing with those animalistic insticts that gave them both a sense of being anti-social. <br>
<br>
Shyriana to be truthful, was excited to see her sister and couldn't wait to get the chance to greet her. Neither was obvious by her emotionless facial expression. Either way, this would prove to be a positive day. Unless.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=empressxena142>EmpressXena142</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of the Tanais River Valley</span><br>  Posts: 251<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/11/03 8:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ausxip.com/graphics/Xena/oaaa1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Valley Upon her Queen's return...</span><hr size=1> -she looked to Yakut's twin sister and smiled as she stepped back from Yakut-my friend I think someone wants to talk to you.-she nodded her head towards Yakut's twin sister Shyriana and her son Skylar- <p>~Xena of Amphipolis<br>
