<br>
Yakut walked over and stood beside Raven. She pulled from her pocket a medallion, a dragon encircling a large raven. It, of course, represented Raven and the Dragon represented the Valley. A symbol that meant the Valley and Yakut would never abandon its War Queen. Yakut handed the medallion to her daughter and turned smiling to her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Raven, you have made me truly proud. You kept our land in tact and stable while I left. Though I never doubted you. I could never thank you enough; you realize how much the Valley means to me and respect it. You are not all I hoped for as my first born you are much better. I couldn't write up a more special daughter than you.&quot;<br>
<br>
She came to embrace her daughter again, held her tight and slid from the hug. Yakut kissed her daughters cheek and walked to her twin, Shyriana.<br>
<br>
&quot;Shy,I missed you. Your something very special to me, always know that. You will always have a home here.&quot; Her green orbs went down to look upon Skylar. &quot;Hey, your always welcome here too, lad. All these women can be intimidating but with your looks they'll melt at your feet.&quot; she chuckled before reaching for her shoulder bag. She pulled out a small chain mail pull over, and handed it to Shy. &quot;Its for Skylar, the male warriors were it in Britannia.&quot; She dug deeper and found a amulet of a tiger, Yakut handed it to Shyriana. &quot;Its something I found on my way I back. I bought it from a Merchant from Carthage. He said, it is supposed to keep ahold of who you are.&quot; She smiled, &quot;I think you can handle that though.&quot; The Shamaness embraced Shyriana and her nephew tightly.<br>
<br>
From there Yakut would have moved to Otere, but her sister was occupied with the newcomer. A smile threatned her features, Otere never ceased to amuse her. Anyway, the Amazon made her way closer to the bonfire. The flames made her green pools seem warm, and the blaze reflected in her gleaming eyes. So much had changed and yet it seemed as if everything was as it was. Yakut knew the truth though, things had changed but it was all for the better.<br>
<br>
The Shamaness stood contemplating, lost in her thoughts til someone felt like disturbing her. <p>-|-Queen Yakut-|-<br>
